post_text: Time is running out to make your vote count in this year’s school board election! If you’ve received a ballot, follow the instructions that came with the ballot and drop it off at the Lincoln State Bank Night Depository or get it postmarked by June 8, 2020. If you haven’t applied for a ballot yet, call the school at 439-2287 between 8AM and 4 PM to get an application and get it turned in.

post_text: If you haven't filled out an Absentee/Mail Ballot Application for the School Board Election yet, time is running short! There are applications available in the north foyer of the High School by the pop machine. You can pick one up and fill it out. There are 4 options to return it to the school: 1) call the school between 8-4 to drop it off, 2) put it in an envelope labeled "School Election" and drop it off in the Wyndmere Lincoln State Bank Night Depository box, 3) email it to shari.hetland@k12.nd.us, OR 4) fax it to 701-439-2804. Once we receive the application back, we will mail a ballot out to you (ballot should also include instructions and TWO envelopes). Please make sure you read and follow the instructions! The ballot must be postmarked by June 8, 2020 or dropped off before 5 PM on June 8, 2020. If you have questions, please call the school at 439-2287.
